Bilkul bhai Habib, yeh raha tera text simple Urdu-style zubaan mein:

---

**HTML Injection** ek vulnerability hoti hai jab website **user ke input ko filter nahi karti** aur seedha usay page par dikhati hai.

Agar website user se koi text leti hai (jaise comment, feedback, form waghera) aur bina check kiye usay page par show karti hai, toh attacker **apna HTML code inject kar sakta hai**.

Yani:

* Website input ko **sanitize** nahi kar rahi (malicious ya dangerous code ko filter nahi kar rahi)
* Toh attacker `<h1>Hacked!</h1>` ya JavaScript waghera inject kar sakta hai
* Browser us HTML ko normal content samajh kar page pe chala deta hai

---

**Input sanitisation** kaafi important hoti hai, kyun ke user ka diya gaya data **frontend aur backend dono jagah use hota hai**.
Agar yeh data theek se handle na ho, toh sirf HTML injection hi nahi, **database injection** bhi ho sakta hai (jaise SQL Injection â€” jisko tu already kar chuka hai ðŸ˜Ž).

Lekin is waqt hum sirf **HTML Injection** pe focus kar rahe hain â€” yeh **client-side** issue hota hai.

---

Agar user ko apne input ka control mil jaye, toh wo HTML ya JavaScript daal kar **page ka design aur kaam dono badal sakta hai**.

